      "role": "user",
      "content": "a dict-based dsu? i tried something like that but with 10^6 nodes the overhead of python dict objects is actually way worse than just using a flat array. the overhead per entry is massive. \n\nthe issue is that the judge is really strict. even with a flat array, maybe 2-3 large arrays get me close to the 64MB limit. is there a way to do this without even needing the full arrays for the parent pointers? or maybe some way to handle the input stream so we don't blow the memory before we even start the DSU? give me the actual code, i tried a basic implementation and it still failed.",
      "source": "evaluator"
